Ghana 2010-11 Cocoa Harvest to Reach Record High at 930,000 Metric Tons

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-05-12T16:50:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/ghana-2010-11-cocoa-harvest-to-reach-record-high-at-930-000-metric-tons.html
Ghana ’s total 2010-11 cocoa harvest
will reach 930,000 metric tons, the highest in the West African
nation’s history, said Yaw Adu-Ampomah, deputy chief executive
of the Ghana Cocoa Board.  The main crop, which ends May 19, will reach 860,000 tons,
while the light, or mid, crop will produce 70,000 tons, he said
by phone from Accra, the capital, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
 mdzawu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
